# RobotCore Sync Rule

When editing robot or NinjaTrader-related files, **always sync changes to `system/RobotCore_For_NinjaTrader`** in the repository root.

## Sync Mapping

| Source | Sync To |
|-------|---------|
| `system/modules/robot/ninjatrader/RobotSimStrategy.cs` | `system/RobotCore_For_NinjaTrader/Strategies/RobotSimStrategy.cs` |
| `system/modules/robot/ninjatrader/RobotSimStrategy.cs` | `%OneDrive%\Documents\NinjaTrader 8\bin\Custom\Strategies\RobotSimStrategy.cs` |

**Do NOT sync RobotSimStrategy to AddOns/RobotCore_For_NinjaTrader** - NinjaTrader compiles AddOns, so that would create duplicate class definitions. Strategy lives only in Custom/Strategies/.
| `system/modules/robot/core/*` (RobotEngine, StreamStateMachine, Execution/*, etc.) | `system/RobotCore_For_NinjaTrader/*` (matching paths) |

## When Making Edits

1. **RobotSimStrategy**: Edit `system/modules/robot/ninjatrader/RobotSimStrategy.cs`, then sync to both:
   - `system/RobotCore_For_NinjaTrader/Strategies/RobotSimStrategy.cs`
   - `OneDrive\Documents\NinjaTrader 8\bin\Custom\Strategies\RobotSimStrategy.cs`

2. **Engine/Core files** (RobotEngine, StreamStateMachine, NinjaTraderSimAdapter, etc.): Edit in `system/modules/robot/core/` and sync to `system/RobotCore_For_NinjaTrader/` (or edit in RobotCore_For_NinjaTrader and sync to system/modules/robot/core/).

3. **NinjaTraderBarRequest**: Lives in `system/modules/robot/ninjatrader/`; copy to NinjaTrader Custom folder as needed.

## Why

`system/RobotCore_For_NinjaTrader` is the primary NinjaTrader DLL build. Keeping it in sync ensures:
- One place to see the full robot codebase
- Build and deploy from `system/RobotCore_For_NinjaTrader`
- No drift between modules and the NT project
